\begin_layout Subsubsection
Calcular el orden de cada elemento de los grupos diédricos 
\begin_inset Formula $\boldsymbol{D_{n}}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Por el teorema de Lagrange, el orden de los elementos debe ser divisor de
 
\begin_inset Formula $2n$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Independientemente de 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

, sabemos que 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|1\right|=1\ y\ \left|b\right|=2$
\end_inset

, pues 
\begin_inset Formula $b^{2}=b\cdot b=a^{\left\lfloor 0\right\rfloor _{n}}b^{\left\lfloor 2\right\rfloor _{2}}=1$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ahora debemos ver el orden de 
\begin_inset Formula $a^{i}$
\end_inset

 y el de 
\begin_inset Formula $a^{i}b$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Esto es equivalente a calcular 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

 tal que 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(a^{i}\right)^{k}=1$
\end_inset

, pues 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(a^{i}\right)^{k+1}=\left(a^{i}\right)^{k}a^{i}=a^{i}$
\end_inset

, y comienza de nuevo el ciclo.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ahora bien, el orden de 
\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset

 es 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

, pues 
\begin_inset Formula $a^{n}=a^{\left\lfloor n\right\rfloor _{n}}=1$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Entonces, por el Lema 4.21, sabemos que
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
k=\left|a^{i}\right|=\frac{\left|a\right|}{mcd\left(\left|a\right|,i\right)}=\frac{n}{mcd\left(n,i\right)}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ahora, el orden de 
\begin_inset Formula $a^{i}b$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Primero calculemos 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|ab\right|$
\end_inset

, tenemos que 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(ab\right)\left(ab\right)=a^{\left\lfloor 1-1\right\rfloor _{n}}b^{\left\lfloor 2\right\rfloor _{2}}=1$
\end_inset

, luego 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|ab\right|=2$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ahora bien, 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(a^{i}b\right)\left(a^{i}b\right)=a^{\left\lfloor i+\left(-1\right)^{1}i\right\rfloor _{n}}b^{\left\lfloor 2\right\rfloor _{2}}=a^{\left\lfloor 0\right\rfloor _{n}}b^{\left\lfloor 0\right\rfloor _{2}}=1$
\end_inset

, luego 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|a^{i}b\right|=2,\ \forall i=1,...,n-1$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

